d 'XTHETEROQUANT': module to compute quantiles of heterogeneous individual-specific coefficients in panel data, with SQB and CDQB bootstrap inference (Galvao, Hounyo and Lin, 2026)
d
d      xtheteroquant implements the two-step estimator of Galvao,
d Hounyo and Lin (2026) for the tau-quantile of the cross-sectional
d    distribution of heterogeneous individual-specific coefficients
d in the linear panel-data model	y_it = a_i + x_it'b_i +
d e_it,        i = 1,...,N,  t = 1,...,T,    where every unit i has
d its own intercept a_i and its own slope vector b_i.  The
d procedure is:        Step 1 (individual estimation).	For each
d unit i, estimate the coefficient vector by OLS using only that
d unit's time series.	     Step 2 (quantile aggregation).  For
d each coefficient, take the empirical tau-quantile of the N
d first-step estimates, 	   theta_hat(tau) = argmin_theta
d (1/N) sum_i rho_tau(theta_hat_i - theta), where rho_tau is the
d quantile-regression check	       function.    Unlike
d conventional fixed-effects quantile regression (qreg / panel QR),
d where tau indexes the conditional distribution of the    outcome,
d here tau indexes the distribution of the structural coefficients
d across units: tau = .9 answers "what is the slope for    the
d 90th-percentile most-responsive unit?", not "what is the effect
d at the 90th percentile of y?".  Typical uses: heterogeneous	
d treatment or policy sensitivities, the distribution of
d mutual-fund timing skill, firm-specific pass-through,
d country-specific    elasticities. 
d
d KW: quantile regression
d KW: heterogeneity
d KW: panel data
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260612
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
f xtheteroquant.ado
f xtheteroquant.sthlp
f xtheteroquant_example.do
